{"id":274043,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Period_(geology)","text":"=\"preserve\">A period in geology is a main subunit of an era.\nThus the Mesozoic era is divided into three periods: the Triassic, the Jurassic and the Cretaceous. These periods are then further subdivided into stages.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Geology","surface_form":"geology","offset":24},{"uri":"Era","surface_form":"era","offset":56},{"uri":"Mesozoic","surface_form":"Mesozoic","offset":70},{"uri":"Triassic","surface_form":"Triassic","offset":118},{"uri":"Jurassic","surface_form":"Jurassic","offset":132},{"uri":"Cretaceous","surface_form":"Cretaceous","offset":149},{"uri":"Stage_(geology)","surface_form":"stages","offset":208}]}